    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Dual Turbocharger and Exhaust Tubing - Installation</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="5">
            <title>Assembly of Turbocharger</title>
            <figure id="f3000325" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj15/J15028.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Align orientation marks</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen both high and low-pressure turbocharger assembles and align turbine mating V-band
                    clamp marks but do not tighten clamp.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place Turbo Crossover Tube Seal Remover / Installer holding fixture into bench vise. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_54.xml" xrefid="E30003C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place crossover tube into holding fixture and tighten clamps.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000326" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj15/J15017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing the large crossover seal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position seal onto crossover tube. Using
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_54.xml" xrefid="te30003C">Turbo Crossover Tube Seal Remover / Installer
                    </hotlnk>
                    , drive seal into crossover tube until seal and tool have seated.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000327" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj15/J15018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing the small crossover seal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a new O-ring seal onto short end of crossover tube.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000328" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj15/J15011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing the crossover tube</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place V-band clamp onto crossover tube as shown.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install crossover tube onto adjacent turbocharger inlet. A slight twisting motion may be
                    necessary to start the long end of tube. It may be necessary to add a soapy solution to seal surface
                    in order to get seal started onto turbocharger inlet.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000329" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj15/J15012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Torquing the turbocharger oil drain tubing bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The turbo oil drain must be installed at this time. It will not interfere with turbocharger
                        alignment during installation.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install both O-ring seals and four bolts (M6 x 25) to oil drain tube. Tighten bolts to
                    the
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_53.xml" xrefid="E30003B">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                    at this time.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
